items.title: Stock Market LIVE Updates: GIFT Nifty indicates a firm start; US markets gain, Asia trade mixed
items.description: Sensex Today | Stock Market LIVE Updates: Wall Street closed higher on Monday ahead of a packed week of earnings from megacap companies and the final stretch before the Nov. 5 presidential election, while sentiment improved after energy supplies were not disrupted by weekend developments in the Middle East. The S&P 500 gained 15.4 points, or 0.27%, to 5,823.52, while the Nasdaq Composite gained 48.58 points, or 0.26%, to 18,567.19. The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 273.17 points, or 0.65%, to 42,387.57.

items.title: Agri Picks Report October 29, 2024: Geojit Financial Services
items.description: According to Geojit, The output of cotton in the kharif season 2024-25 (Jul-Jun) in Rajasthan is expected to be up nearly 134% at 6.1 million tonnes from 2.6 million tonnes in the kharif season last year, according to the first advance estimates of area, production and yield released by the state's agriculture department.

items.title: Live: Nifty Recovers Over 300 Points, Back Near 24,500 Led By Banks| Maruti Disappoints|Closing Bell
items.description:
Nifty makes a strong comeback, rebounding near the 24,500 mark with broader markets recovering losses. Midcaps rally nearly 1%, and PSU banks extend gains. Nifty Bank jumps over 1,000 points, while metals surge on reports of possible Chinese stimulus. However, autos, FMCG, IT, and pharma sectors remain under pressure.
Join Nandita Khemka and Yatin Mota as they dive into stocks on their radar and discuss the day's top movers!

items.description: On the sectoral front, bank, realty, power, capital goods were up 1-2 percent, while pharma, IT and auto down 0.5-1 percent.
